name: Squat
description: lowers their hips from a standing position and then stands back up

name: Lunges
description: refer to any position of the human body where one leg is positioned forward with knee bent and foot flat on the ground while the other leg is not positioned behind

name: Side Lunges
description: Start standing with legs slightly wider than shoulder-distance apart and toes pointed forward. Shift your body weight to one leg bending the knee until it reaches a 90-degree angle and the other leg is straight. Glutes are pressing back behind you. Return to center and switch sides.

name: Calf Raise
description: Stand up straight, then push through the balls of your feet and raise your heel until you are standing on your toes. Then lower slowly back to the start. For this reason, calf raises are just about the easiest exercise to slip into your day-to-day life.

name: Plank
description: Go into a plank formation

name: Side Plank
description: Go onto your side in a plank formation

name: Side leg raises
description: Raise legs up and down

name: Raised Leg Hold
description: Raise legs up while lying down and then hold for 20 seconds

name: Flutter Kick
description: Point legs out in a 45 degree angle and move feet up and down to look like you are kicking

name: Alternate Side Plank
description: Switch your position from side plank on one arm to plank on both arms and back to side plank on another arm

name: Anterior Raises Alternating
description: Raise arm in a forward position in an alternating manner

name: Anterior Raises
description: Raise both arms in a forward position together

name: Behind back shrugs
description: Put arms behind your waist and contract your back and shoulder

name: Lateral raises
description: Raise arms to the side until neck level

name: Pike Push Ups
description: Get into a pike position and do push ups

name: Elevated Pike Push Ups
description: Get into a pike position with your toes on top of an object and do push ups

name: Face Pulls
description: Pull resistance bands towards your face

name: Military Press
description: Put weights at the side of your head and push upwards

name: Rear Delt Flies
description: Lower your chest to a 45 degree position, and push the weights towards your rear

name: Handstand hold on the wall
description: Kick your feet onto the wall and hold the position

name: Mountain Climbers
description: Get in a push up position and bring your feet to your chest in an alternating manner

name: Push Up to Plank
description: Switch alternatingly between push up position and plank position

name: Wall Plank
description: Put your legs on the wall and hold a plank

name: Shoulder Taps
description: Get into a push up position and bring arms to chest alternatingly

name: Australian Pull Ups
description: Use a pull up bar at waist level and pull the bar towards your chest with a pull grip

name: Australian Chin Ups
description: Use a pull up bar at waist level and pull the bar towards your chest with a curl grip

name: Jumping Pull Ups
description: Jump towards the bar and do a pull up

name: Jumping Chin Ups
description: Jump towards the bar and do a chin up

name: Negative Pull Up
description: Get into the peak of a pull up position and resist going back into a relaxed position gradually

name: Negative Chin Up
description: Get into the peak of a chin up position and resist going back into a relaxed position gradually

name: Pull Up
description: Get into a hanging position and pull until your head is over the bar

name: Chin Up
description: Get into a hanging position and curl until your head is over the bar

name: Superman Hold
description: Get into a prone position and raise your arms and legs as much as possible and hold

name: Superman Pumps
description: Get into a prone position and raise your arms and legs as much as possible and hold and relax alternatingly

name: Butterflies
description: Get into a prone position and rotate your arms like a butterfly

name: Scapula Shrugs
description: Get into a hanging position contract your scapulas

name: Parallel Rows
description: Lower your back to 45 degrees and pull the weights toward your chest

name: Reverse Flies
description: Lower your back to 45 degrees and push the weights towards your sides
